When you go out on a clear blue ocean, you're actually gazing at a microbial soup full of vibrant life. What you see here are marine bacteria buzzing about and exploring other members of the Marine food Web. To emphasize how small this world really is, I've added a white line to most of my slides that shows you the thickness of a single strand of human hair. Very tiny.
